# Concept Note Structure Prompt

Generate a Concept note for an evergreen concept.

## Concept Data
- Concept Name: {{CONCEPT_NAME}}
- Source Note Name: {{SOURCE_NOTE_NAME}}
- Source Display Title: {{SOURCE_DISPLAY_TITLE}}
- Language: {{LANGUAGE}}
- Tags: {{TAGS}}
- Related Concepts: {{RELATED_CONCEPTS}}
- MoC Targets: {{MOC_TARGETS}}

## OUTPUT FORMAT

Generate the full markdown file content.

Format rules:
- status: evergreen (not draft)
- type: concept
- date_created: today's date
- last_updated: today's date
- sources: list with wikilink to source note
- tags: always include "concept", then topic tags from the plan

If language is zh (Chinese):
- sections: 核心概念, 背景, 关联
- Include bilingual headings: ## English / ## 中文
- title_en: English title in frontmatter if available
- language: zh

If language is en:
- sections: Core concept, Context, Links

Core concept content: Write 2-3 sentences describing what this concept is, why it matters, and how it connects to the source material. Use flowing prose, not bullet points.

Context content: Write 1-2 paragraphs of flowing prose describing the background, significance, and connections to other concepts. Reference related concepts with wikilinks like [[Concept Name]].

Links content: List wikilinks to related MoCs and existing concepts.

Output ONLY the markdown file content, no explanation.
